message.name: ID_FILE_NAME_INVALID
message.locale: The file name supplied is invalid.
message.cause: The value for the file name entered was null or empty.
message.action: You must enter a valid file name that exists and is exact.

message.name: ID_EXECUTION_OBJECT_DELETE_ERROR
message.locale: Unable to delete the IEG script execution object.
message.cause: Unable to delete the recorded IEG script execution object as it does not exist.
message.action: Make sure the object was not previously deleted

message.name: ID_IMPORT_FAILED_CYCLE
message.locale: The import failed because the following scripts form a cycle: %1s.
message.cause: A script is defined as a subscript of an ancestor.
message.action: Check the scripts that are being imported

message.name: ID_IMPORT_FAILED_UNDEFINED
message.locale: The import failed because the script '%1s' has a subscript '%2s' which doesn't exist.
message.cause: A script has a dependency on an unexisting subscript.
message.action: Check the scripts that are being imported

message.name: ID_IMPORT_FAILED_SCRIPT_WITH_SAME_NAME_ALREADY_EXISTS
message.locale: The import failed because the a script with the name '%1s' already exists. The specified script name must be unique.
message.cause: A script with the same name already exists on the database.
message.action: Specify a different script name when importing.

message.name: ID_IMPORT_FAILED_PARSER
message.locale: The import failed because of parsing problems.

message.name: ID_DIRECTORY_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: The IEG directory '%1s' does not exist.
message.cause: The directory that you specified does not exist.
message.action: Be sure that the name and path of the directory is exact.

message.name: ID_DIRECTORY_NAME_INVALID
message.locale: The directory name supplied is invalid.
message.cause: The value for the directory entered was null or empty.
message.action: You must enter a valid directory name and path that exists and is exact.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_MODIFICATION_ERROR
message.locale: You cannot delete this Script. It is referenced by '%1s'.
message.cause: Script is referenced by at least one script.
message.action: Remove the referencing scripts.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_ALREADY_EXISTS
message.locale: A script with the ID '%1s' already exists.
message.cause: The script already exists with that ID, that you are trying to import.
message.action: Be sure that the ID of the script is correct, and that it doesn't already exist.

message.name: ID_UNKNOWN_SCRIPT
message.locale: Question script with ID '%1s' does not exist.
message.cause: script with given script ID does not exist
message.action: Be sure that the script ID Exists

message.name: ID_CLUSTER_ELEMENT_NOT_DEFINED
message.locale: The element '%1s' has not been defined for the cluster '%2s'.
message.cause: The element has not been defined for this cluster.
message.action: Be sure that the element belongs to the specified cluster.

message.name: ID_CLUSTER_ELEMENT_ALREADY_DEFINED
message.locale: Element '%1s' has already been defined for cluster '%2s'.
message.cause: The specified element has already been used for this cluster.
message.action: Be sure that the cluster is referenced correctly.

message.name: ID_CLUSTER_NOT_DEFINED
message.locale: Cluster '%1s' has not been defined for question page '%2s'.
message.cause: The cluster specified could not be found.
message.action: Be sure that the reference ID for the cluster is exact.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_RELATIONSHIP_ALREADY_EXISTS
message.locale: A relationship between the scripts '%1s' and '%2s' already exists.
message.cause: There was already a relationship existing between the specified scripts.
message.action: Be sure that the scripts exist, and that they are not already related.

message.name: ID_ROOT_ENTITY_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: The root entity for this script could not be found.

message.name: ID_DATA_STORE_NOT_OPENED
message.locale: The common data store could not be opened.

message.name: ID_SCHEMA_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: The specified schema could not be found.
message.cause: The common data store could not find the schema specified.
message.action: Ensure that the schema is correctly specified and matches the declaration in the IEG script.

message.name: ID_ENTITY_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: An entity could not be found in the common data store.
message.cause: The common data store could not find the entity specified.
message.action: Informational Only

message.name: ID_ENTITY_TYPE_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: The entity '%1s' could not be found in the common data store.
message.cause: The common data store could not find the entity specified.
message.action: Ensure the entity name in the schema matches the entity in the IEG script.

message.name: ID_ENTITY_TYPE_NOT_DEFINED
message.locale: The entity '%1s' is not defined in the schema.
message.cause: The entity that was specified is not defined in the schema..
message.action: Ensure the entity name matches an entity in the schema.

message.name: ID_PERSON_ENTITY_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: A Person entity could not be found in the common data store.
message.cause: The common data store could not find the entity specified.
message.action: Informational Only

message.name: ID_ATTRIBUTE_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: An attribute '%1s' of entity '%2s' could not be found in the common data store.
message.cause: The common data store could not find the attribute specified.
message.action: Informational Only

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_FILE_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: The IEG script file '%1s' does not exist.
message.cause: The file that you specified does not exist.
message.action: Be sure that the name of the file is exact.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_EXECUTION_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: The IEG script execution '%1s' does not exist.
message.cause: The IEG script execution that you specified does not exist.
message.action: Be sure that the ID of the script execution is correct.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_EXECUTION_NOT_READABLE
message.locale: The IEG script execution '%1s' can't be read from the database.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_EXECUTION_NOT_WRITABLE
message.locale: The IEG script execution '%1s' can't be written to the database.

message.name: ID_UNMARSHALL_ERROR
message.locale: Unable to unmarshal the data. The error message is '%1s'.
message.cause: A problem occurred while `unmarshalling` data
message.action: Informational only

message.name: ID_ANSWERS_NOT_FOR_CURRENT_PAGE
message.locale: The answers provided are not for the current page.
message.cause: The answers returned are not for the current page.
message.action: The answers you entered are not for the current question file, be sure to make it the exact question file.

message.name: ID_ACTION_LINK_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: The action link specified could not be found.
message.cause: The action link encountered by the IEG player could not be found or is the wrong type.
message.action: Informational only

message.name: ID_ACTION_LINK_PAGE_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: The question page specified by the action link, '%1s', was not encountered during script execution.
message.cause: The action link selected does not refer to a page that was encountered during script execution.
message.action: Ensure that the action link refers to a page that was encountered during script execution.

message.name: ID_INVALID_ACTION_LINK
message.locale: An invalid action link was encountered during script execution.
message.cause: An action link was not placed in either a cluster or a list.
message.action: Ensure that all action links are only placed in either clusters or lists.

message.name: ID_DOB_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: Age could not be determined because a value for 'Person.dateOfBirth' could not be found in the datastore.
message.cause: A 'dateOfBirth' attribute needs to be present on the Person entity in order to determine age.
message.action: Specify 'dateOfBirth' on the Person entity.

message.name: ID_INVALID_ENTITY_ID
message.locale: The entity id '%1s' is invalid.
message.cause: The entity id is not in the correct form..
message.action: Ensure that the entity id is specified in the form 'EnityName.AttributeName'.

message.name: ID_INVALID_EXPRESSION
message.locale: The expression '%1s' is invalid.
message.cause: The expression specified must be a Boolean expression.
message.action: Ensure that all attributes in the expression are mandatory or have a default value.

message.name: ID_INVALID_EXPRESSION_WITH_CAUSE
message.locale: The expression '%1s' is invalid. %2s.
message.action: Ensure that all attributes in the expression are mandatory or have a default value. Each attribute must be specified on an entity in the associated datastore schema.

message.name: ID_DIRECTORY_CREATION_FAILED
message.locale: The output directory %1s couldn't be created.
message.cause: An existing output directory has to be supplied, or the necessary rights to create it must exist.
message.action: Supply an existing output directory or check that creation rights exist.

message.name: RUN_QUERYEXPRESSION
message.locale: Query expression must be Boolean: %1s

message.name: RUN_IOEXCEPTION
message.locale: IOException while loading store: %1s

message.name: ID_ERR_INVOKING_CUSTOM_OUTPUT_DATA_ACCESSOR
message.locale: There was an error while trying to invoke the custom output data accessor %1s
message.cause: There was an error while trying to invoke the custom output data accessor.
message.action: Ensure the custom output data accessor has been configured correctly.

message.name: RUN_PLAYERBEHAVIOUR_INSTANTIATION_EXCEPTION
message.locale: Could not instantiate the player behaviour class %1s.
message.cause: There was an error while trying to instantiate the player behaviour.
message.action: Ensure that the class exists, is correctly named and implements the correct interface.

message.name: INFO_ID_IEG_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_VALID
message.locale: The specified IEG script definition is valid.
message.cause: Text Only
message.action: For informational use only.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_CANNOT_BE_VALIDATED_AGAINST_SELECTED_SCHEMA
message.locale: The IEG script definition can not be validated against the selected schema.
message.cause: The IEG script definition can not be validated against the selected schema.
message.action: Select an appropriate datastore schema with which to validate the IEG script definition.

message.name: ID_INVALID_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_ENTITY_NOT_PRESENT_IN_DATASTORE
message.locale: The entity named '%1s' specified in the IEG script definition is not present in the associated datastore schema.
message.cause: The entity specified in the script definition is not present in the associated datastore schema.
message.action: Either the IEG script must be updated to specify the entity or the associated datastore schema must be updated to include the entity.

message.name: ID_INVALID_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_PARENT_CHILD_ENTITY_RELATIONSHIP
message.locale: The IEG script definition entity relationship between the parent entity named '%1s' and the child entity named '%2s' is invalid. No such parent child entity relationship exists in the associated datastore schema.
message.cause: The specified parent child entity relationship in the IEG script definition is invalid as no such relationship exists in the associated datastore schema.
message.action: Either the IEG script must be updated to specify the correct parent child entity relationship or the associated datastore schema must be updated to include the valid parent child relationship.

message.name: ID_INVALID_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_MULTIPLE_RELATIONSHIP_PARENT
message.locale: The IEG script definition entity relationship between the parent entity named '%1s' and the child entity named '%2s' is invalid. A '%2s' entity cannot have multiple parents when a relationship-page is used.
message.cause: The specified parent child entity relationship in the IEG script definition is invalid as it can only be used in one context when a relationship-page is used.
message.action: The IEG script and the associated datastore schema must be updated to define a different child entity name to be used in contexts other than relationship-page and relationship-summary-list.

message.name: ID_INVALID_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_ATTRIBUTE_DOES_NOT_EXIST_ON_ENTITY
message.locale: The attribute named '%1s' associated with the entity '%2s' in the IEG script definition is invalid. No such entity attribute relationship exists in the associated datastore schema.
message.cause: The attribute associated with the specified entity in the script definition is not present in the associated datastore schema.
message.action: Either the IEG script must be updated to specify a valid attribute for the entity or the associated datastore schema must be updated to specify a valid attribute for that entity.

message.name: ID_INVALID_DATASTORE_REQUIRED_RELATIONSHIP_ENTITY_NOT_PRESENT
message.locale: The entity named '%1s' must be present in the datastore schema to allow relationship data to be captured or displayed.
message.cause: The Person or Relationship entities are not present in the datastore but there is a relationship page present in the script.
message.action: Either the IEG script must be updated to remove the relationship pages or the associated datastore schema must be updated to specify the required entities.

message.name: ID_INVALID_DATASTORE_REQUIRED_RELATIONSHIP_ENTITY_ATTRIBUTE_NOT_PRESENT
message.locale: The attribute named '%1s' must be present on the entity named '%2s' when relationship data is being captured or displayed.
message.cause: The correct Relationship entity attribute is not present in the datastore but there is a relationship page present in the script containing a question.
message.action: Either the IEG script must be updated to remove the relationship page question or the associated datastore schema must be updated to specify the required entity attribute.

message.name: ID_REQUIRED_RELATIONSHIP_ENTITY_ATTRIBUTE_FOR_QUESTION_NOT_PRESENT
message.locale: The attribute named '%1s' must be present on the entity named '%2s' when a question data is being captured or displayed on a relationship page.
message.cause: The correct Relationship entity attribute is not present in the datastore but there is a relationship page present in the script containing a question.
message.action: Either the IEG script must be updated to remove the relationship page question or the associated datastore schema must be updated to specify the required entity attribute.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_INVALID_AGAINST_IEG_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_SCHEMA
message.locale: The IEG script definition is invalid against the schema. The schema error is "%1s"
message.cause: The IEG script definition is invalid against the schema.
message.action: The IEG script definition needs to be updated to make it valid against the IEG script definition schema.

message.name: ID_VISITED_PAGES_NOT_UPDATED_CORRECTLY
message.locale: The list of visited pages is inconsistent with the operation being performed.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_ELEMENT_VALIDATOR_NOT_SPECIFIED
message.locale: A validator has not been specified for the script element of type %1s.
message.cause: A validator has not been specified for this script element.
message.action: Informational Only

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_IDENTIFIER_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The script identifier must be specified.
message.cause: A script identifier must be specified for the operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a identifier for the IEG script definition.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_VERSION_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The script version must be specified.
message.cause: A script version must be specified for the operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a version for the IEG script definition.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_TYPE_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The script type must be specified.
message.cause: A script type must be specified for the operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a type for the IEG script definition.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_NAME_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The script name must be specified.
message.cause: A script name must be specified for the operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a name for the IEG script definition.

message.name: ID_SCHEMA_NAME_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The schema name must be specified.
message.cause: A schema name must be specified for the operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a schema name.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_EXECUTION_IDENTIFIER_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The script execution identifier must be supplied.
message.cause: A script execution identifier must be specified for the operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a script execution identifier.

message.name: ID_CLONE_SCRIPT_IDENTIFIER_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The new script identifier to be used to clone the script definition must be specified.
message.cause: A new script identifier must be specified for the clone script definition operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a new identifier for the cloned IEG script definition.

message.name: ID_CLONE_SCRIPT_VERSION_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The new script version to be used to clone the script definition must be specified.
message.cause: A new script version must be specified for the clone script definition operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a new version for the cloned IEG script definition.

message.name: ID_CLONE_SCRIPT_TYPE_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The new script type to be used to clone the script definition must be specified.
message.cause: A new script type must be specified for the clone script definition operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a new type for the cloned IEG script definition.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_TO_BE_CLONED_DOES_NOT_EXIST
message.locale: The script definition with identifier '%1s', version '%2s' and type '%3s' does not exist and therefore cannot be cloned.
message.cause: The script definition specified to be cloned does not exist.
message.action: Choose another script definition to clone.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_DEFINITION_TO_CLONE_TO_ALREADY_EXISTS
message.locale: A script definition with identifier '%1s', version '%2s' and type '%3s' already exists and therefore this script identifier cannot be used for the cloned script definition identifier.
message.cause: The script definition to clone to already exists.
message.action: A different script definition identifier should be specified for the cloned script definition.

message.name: ID_QUESTION_PAGE_IDENTIFIER_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The question page identifier must be specified.
message.cause: A question page identifier must be specified for the operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a identifier for the question page.

message.name: ID_QUESTION_IDENTIFIER_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The question identifier must be specified.
message.cause: A question identifier must be specified for the operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a identifier for the question.

message.name: ID_LOCALE_NOT_SUPPLIED
message.locale: The locale must be specified.
message.cause: A locale must be specified for the operation to succeed.
message.action: Supply a locale.

message.name: ID_QUESTION_CANNOT_BE_FOUND_ON_PAGE
message.locale: The question with identifier '%1s' cannot be found on the page with identifier '%2s'.
message.cause: The question cannot be found on the specified page.
message.action: Supply a valid page and question.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_NOTES_ATTRIBUTE_NOT_FOUND
message.locale: A scriptNotes attribute must exist in the datastore
message.cause: A scriptNotes attribute must exist on the Application entity in the datastore schema in order to use script notes.
message.action: Add a script notes attribute to the Application entity in the datastore schema.

message.name: ID_SCRIPT_QUESTION_TYPE_BOOLEAN_AND_MANDATORY
message.locale: The question with identifier '%1s' and internal identifier '%2s' has type Boolean and marked as mandatory.It will not be possible to select No as the answer for this question in the player as there will be only one check box selectable.
message.cause: The question has type Boolean and marked as mandatory.
message.action: Please mark the question as not mandatory.

message.name: ID_DEPRECATION_CANNOT_VALIDATE_EXPRESSION
message.locale: Cannot validate expression '%1s'.
message.cause: An expression could not be validated
message.action: Check the expression is syntactically valid.

message.name: ID_DEPRECATION_CANNOT_VALIDATE_SCRIPT
message.locale: Cannot validate script.
message.cause: A script could not be validated
message.action: Check the script file contains well-formed XML.

message.name: ERR_SCRIPT_CURRENTLY_EXECUTING
message.locale: This script cannot be deleted because there is an instance currently in execution.
message.cause: An instance of this script is currently executing.
message.action: Complete all existing instances of this script.

message.name: ERR_BOM_SUBSCRIPT_DOESNT_EXIST
message.locale: A relationship between the script '%1s' and its subscript '%1s' cannot be added as the subscript doesn't exist.

message.name: ERR_BOM_DOES_NOT_EXIST
message.locale: The script does not exist.

message.locale: The subscript file %1s is read only and cannot be overwritten.

message.locale: [deprecation comment] %1s

message.locale: %1s at line %2d in the IEG script definition XML file.

message.locale: Row help was specified on the inner list '%1s' of a nested list.
message.cause: It is not valid to specify row help on the inner list of a nested list.
message.action: Ensure that row help is only specified for the outer list of a nested list.

message.name: ID_INVALID_DATATYPE
message.locale: Invalid data type '%1s'.
message.cause: The data type could not be recognized.
message.action: Be sure that the data type you entered is in line with the data types used within the framework.

message.name: ID_DOMAIN_INITIALIZATION_FAILED
message.locale: Domain definition initialization failed.
message.cause: Domain Initialization failed due to the following domainException being thrown: '%1s'
message.action: Use the additional Information supplied by the error to help fix it.

message.name: DUPLICATE_DOMAINS_FOUND_EXCEPTION
message.locale: One or more new duplicate domains were found.
message.cause: When running the tool to detect whether duplicate domains exist between the Curam model and Curam datastore, one or more new duplicate domains were found.
message.action: Ensure any domains that have been configured are uniquely named.

message.name: DUPLICATE_DOMAINS_FOUND_ERROR
message.locale: ERROR: Duplicate domain found
message.cause: When running the tool to detect whether duplicate domains exist between the Curam model and Curam datastore, one or more new duplicate domains were found.
message.action: Ensure any domains that have been configured are uniquely named.

message.name: DUPLICATE_DOMAINS_FOUND_WARNING
message.locale: WARNING: Known duplicate domain detected
message.cause: When running the tool to detect whether duplicate domains exist between the Curam model and Curam datastore, one or more pre-existing duplicate domains were found.
message.action: This message is for informational purposes only.

message.name: ERR_INVALID_QUESTION_ID
message.locale: The question id '%1s' is invalid.
